  "prompt": "What is there beyond the asteroid belt?",
  "response": "Beyond the asteroid belt, there are several significant objects and regions in our solar system:\n\n1. Jupiter\n- The largest planet in our solar system\n- First of the outer planets\n- Has numerous moons\n\n2. Outer Planets\n- Saturn (with its extensive ring system)\n- Uranus\n- Neptune\n\n3. Kuiper Belt\n- A region beyond Neptune's orbit\n- Contains many small, icy bodies\n- Home to dwarf planets like Pluto, Haumea, and Makemake\n\n4. Scattered Disc\n- An area overlapping with the outer edge of the Kuiper Belt\n- Contains icy objects with more eccentric orbits\n\n5. Oort Cloud\n- A hypothesized spherical cloud of icy objects\n- Located at the outermost edge of the solar system\n- Thought to be the source of long-period comets\n\n6. Trans-Neptunian Objects (TNOs)\n- Various dwarf planets and smaller icy bodies\n- Located beyond Neptune's orbit\n\nBeyond our solar system lies interstellar space, which contains other star systems and eventually leads to other galaxies.",
